tomach.  But I do not faltar, I make haste to West Commonlands and leave the rotting stench of the woods.  It is here that I feel free.  I remember when I was wee, the Commonlands were dangerous for m'travels.  Griffons and giants all around, scary, yes, scary.  Sprinting quickly past the Dervish Cutthroats, I see my target ahead.  East Commonlands, the marketplace of Norrath.  <br>
<br>
The place is busier than usual this day.  Races and professions of all sorts gather here to sell their hard earned treasures in hopes of acquiring new ones.  Always an interesting negotiation going on in these parts.  I enter the tunnel to find m'Brethren awaiting me.  The Avatar herself, Chrysania hugs me with a smile, the good druid Belrich cackles gleefully at me (to this day I am unsure if he laughs at me or with me), the noble Shaman and Justicar, Alysandir punts me across the tunnel, for he is my blood brother and it has come to be an event between us.  I would punt him, but he's a tad to tall for me to get a leg on.  I see my pal Bucco, a great Magician whom I travelled the lands with many a time, he greets me with his trademark, &quot;Hullo&quot;.  I give the Ranger, Deral a nice wedgie to start our travels.  He groans at the sight of me, but 'tis fun to mess with him.  I enjoy his company and feel safe when en route with him.  There is the Warrior, Santhar who waves his sword at my face and threatens to riposte me.  The Ranger Aatrex sits in the corner drinking a fine ale and nearby I salute Aedwy the Monk and Rinala the Shamaness, the young couple soon to be married.  All around I see my Brethren.  a good bunch they are.  Near a torch, I spot Galuvyen, practicing his druidic magics silently.  Galuvyen is flanked by the fine Paldins of the Brethren, Falkieri, Kelindill, Skyreaver, and Carlino.  Seems the noble Skyreaver is looking into creating a fine set of Ro armor.  Falkieri and Kelindill are sure to help his cause.  My eyes grow wide as I see the Huntress, m'lady Grindess walk toward me with a smile.  I greet her warmly as we share a honey mead together.  A grand adventure we will have, yes, yes.  A grand one indeed!  <br>
<br>
I pause for a moment as a well-seasoned Wizard auctions his hard earned treasures.  &quot;Golden Efreeti Boots, here!&quot;, he says with a grin.  I drool all over m'armor and ask the man his price.  &quot;Yes, these fine boots can be yours for a mere 10,000 platinums&quot;, he states firmly.  I think to myself, &quot;Bah, mebbe in a few seasons&quot;, and go about my business.<br>
<br>
Looking to my right I see the newest members of the Dawn.  I see Ozzander the Enchanter.  His powerful magics memorized in his brilliant mind.  I see m'Brethren all around and can't wait for our journey to begin.  The journey is set to embark as we make our way to the Lost temple of Cazic-Thule.  To journey together as a family and to explore the great unknown.  That is why I am here.  that is why the Brethren are my family.  <br>
<br>
This is what being a Halfling, a Cleric, and a Brethren is all about.  Drink some fine ales, tell some good tales, travel to far away lands, and to explore the unknown.  The purpose is to destroy evil.  The path is through the Dawn.  The heart is with the Brethren.<br>
<br>
Thank you m'Brethren.  Our travels and adventures together are all that truly matters.<br>
<br>
Jeppo Curefinger<br>
Your Knight Commander<br>
